<BLOCK>
The name of your medicine is 'Zestoretic'10. It contains lisinopril, which is one of a group of medicines called "angiotensin converting enzyme inhibitors" or "ACE inhibitors" for short. It also contains hydrochlorothiazide which is a diuretic. This combination of medicines is used to treat high blood pressure.
</BLOCK>

