<BLOCK>
What's in vour medicine?
</BLOCK>


<BLOCK>
'Zestoretic' 10 tablets are peach coloured and they contain 10 mg of lisinopril and 12.5 mg of hydrochlorothiazide. The tablets also contain the following ingredients which have no effect: calcium hydrogen phosphate, iron oxide, magnesium stearate, maize starch and mannitol.
</BLOCK>


